According to the ambassador, the Czechs have a reputation as Eurosceptics and people perceive the negative aspects rather than the positive ones.
In addition, he regretted the low participation of Czechs in the European institutions.
The blame is on a multitude of factors, such as the modesty of our candidates, their inability to write motivational messages, but also the lack of support from the Czechs.
In addition to the success of the Czech presidency, he highlighted the strength and collaboration of the Visegrad Group.
"Believe me, when a Pole and a Hungarian come to me and a Slovak approaches me, a Frenchman next to me says to me: 'What, have you already stayed, those of the Visegrad Group?'
In the future, the EU, according to Vicenová, awaits tough new budgetary policy regulations for the Member States.
It is perceived as something very real of the concept of the two speeds, if not more, in Europe, more than the new "European Federation".
“We have countries in the Eurozone and countries outside the Eurozone.”
"We have the Schengen area and we also have the enhanced cooperation procedure."
“It was said for the first time that only those countries that want to cooperate and those that don’t, should stay out.”
"These procedures will become more and more and will strengthen the two-speed Europe," Vicenová is expected to say.
In this sense, he also highlighted the role of the Czech Republic and Herman van Rompuy in the application of the principle, according to which all issues affecting the whole of the EU should be discussed among member states, not only among the members of the Eurozone.
