Women's Worst Vices: Do They Also Refer to You?
If you ask men to be able to cite some typical vices of women, in general each of them will name them without thinking.
Dear women, do you recognize yourselves in the following lines, where certain feminine vices are cited that get men to boil their blood?
Go Shopping
Do you blame your significant other for being dependent on shopping?
Do you have to buy at least one transplant a week?
Do you like to shop often on sales?
Then in your case you can say that shopping has become a vice.
Some women realize that they should appease their passion for shopping, at least a little.
But look, what woman could resist the temptation to simply walk through the clothing stores, look for well-fitting clothes and then try them all on in the fitting room (ideally in all different colors)?
Although for most women shopping is a hobby, for men it can become practically a hell.
Just remember how many times you have already told your partner to better wait for you at the door.
The Constant Dissatisfaction
"Am I not too fat?"
"I would need to lose at least five pounds - should I start exercising?"
“Do you really like me?”
Do you not hear these phrases?
Is that so?
So she's one of those women who's obsessed with her looks.
It’s not that you should stop taking care of yourself, but many men are allergic to hearing their partner complain all the time about their physical appearance.
The stronger sex also agrees that the more the frequency of complaints increases, the more annoying women become.
Cleanliness and order in the first place
It's like an infinite merry-go-round.
Clean the windows, vacuum, scrub the floor, dust, scrub the bathtub and all that at least twice a week.
Do you blame your partner for stepping on the clean floor with a dirty foot, your children for soiling a freshly cleaned sink and a shelf with glass doors that cost you so much to clean?
In case you suffer this "deviation", try to be aware that nothing should be exaggerated and that order and cleanliness should surely not be paramount in the family.
This harmless desire for cleanliness could threaten your relationships and family well-being.
Making Unpleasant Comments
"Used underpants are left with dirty clothes."
"Do you want to wear those used socks tomorrow too?"
"Wet cloth is not left on the floor!"
If you make those quotes to your partner more times a day, know that you will get him out of your boxes.
Naturally, you don't want to say anything bad, you just want to get everything in order.
Perhaps, if men knew this, women, for their part, would not make so many comments.
Slander and gossip
Some women also suffer from slander, gossip, but also offenses and conspiracies against someone.
Women focus on relationships, so they like to talk together about things like who, where, with whom, how and why.
Perhaps each of us sometimes misses a small and harmless gossip.
With the hand in the heart, this is typical of almost all women.
On the other hand, there are gossipy women of those who are not controlled, who love to gossip and do so often, despise everyone and are dangerous to those around them, especially in a female work team.
