So was the work of the cale<0xC3><0xB1>o who identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A lofoscopist from Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is key.
On November 4, a lofoscopist from the CTI of Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the identity of the FARC’s top leader: “Alfonso Cano”, through the matching of his fingerprints.
Of the seven lofoscopists who work in the CTI section, that week it was the turn of "availability" to Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the area of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the municipalities of Choc<0xC3><0xB3>, where he often had to spend more than five days in the jungle to reach the site where the bodies were to be identified.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after completing the corresponding courses, specialized in lophoscopy, which is the study of the skin of friction, that is, the palms of the hands and feet.
The week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano to Eliazar warned him to wear minimum clothes for three days.
Something big was waiting for him.
Friday night he left for Cauca in a helicopter from Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected to be the man who led the oldest guerrilla in the world, so they asked him to carry the decadactyl card of Guillermo Le<0xC3><0xB3>n Sáenz (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the investigation team at the site where the body was located, he did not recognize it because of its physical appearance, as it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He was beardless, dressed like a local peasant, without glasses and much thinner.
But fingerprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a transplanter and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the fingerprints on the corpse to those on the card.
His eye did not fail him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was in charge of confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinz<0xC3><0xB3>n, that he was the head of the FARC.
In Search of the Footprint
For a typist from the Sikhin of Cali, the recognition made by President Juan Manuel Santos to Eliazar González, in the press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don’t know our work.
Fingerprinting is an exact science, with no margin for error, which can become key in solving crimes.
Apart from identifying corpses, lofoscopists support investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When caught, many offenders present false IDs or have no papers.
We take their fingerprints and look them up in the database.
The investigator said that, in a case of theft, he had to remove a piece of wall from a house, because in that place the thief had supported his hand to take out a safe full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces to make a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to obtain the fingerprint of the entire hand and identify the offender, who had participated in different thefts," he recalled.
Fingerprints can also rule out or reassert suspects in homicide cases.
They recently found a dead man, with bottles of liquor all around him.
Through the investigation it was determined that a relative could be a suspect in the crime and, indeed, a fingerprint on the bottle matched.
Although this does not guarantee that he was the killer, it does place him at the scene of the crime.
A CTI typist explained that in objects "the fingerprints are taken with chemical or physical reagents."
When they appear, a transplanter or tape is used to lift them.
After this, the prints are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registrar.
“The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians,” said the CTI expert.
He clarified that not everything is as shown on the TV show CSI.
Just as not everything that shines is gold, not everything that is touched becomes a trace.
However, if it can be used, if the respective matching is performed.
