However, the real revulsion of the Japanese economy is not based exclusively on the Keynesian impulse that invites us to take advantage of crises to strengthen - or rebuild - infrastructure, to use the shortcomings to grow from scratch.
Japan has woken up, above all, thanks to the evolution of domestic consumption, which currently accounts for 60% of Japanese GDP.
This variable increased by 1%, driven by the increase in spending on vehicles, travel and leisure activities.
