Tokyo has been entrusted to the domestic market, when the yen - the Japanese currency - has become one of the "safe haven values" chosen by investors fleeing the debt crisis in the euro zone and the murky forecasts of the US, a privilege that weighs like a slab in the accounts of exporting companies.
